x4freetext: 50 M GUIDE TUBE, RADIUS OF CURVATURE 2.85 KM,
NEUTRON BEAM DIAMETER OF 18.6 MM WITH A NEUTRON RATE
MEASUREMENT OF GAMMAS FROM THERMAL CAPTURE.
.SI(LI) DETECTOR, VOLUME 1 CC AND AREA 200 MM-SQ,
SHIELDED WITH LIF (ENRICHED IN 6-LI) AND PB, PLACED
15.5 CM FROM THE TARGET. ENERGY RESOLUTION 300 EV FWHM
AT 17 KEV AND 350 EV FWHM AT 30 KEV. THE ABSOLUTE
EFFICIENCY WAS DETERMINED WITH SPECIAL CALIBRATED
EACH INDIVIDUAL SPECTRUM WERE CALIBRATED WITH K AND L
X-RAY LINES OF THE TARGET ELEMENT, THE 30.6 KEV LINE
OF AL AND PREVIOUSLY MEASURED GAMMA LINES.
COUNTS IN THE LINES, THE MEASURING TIMES (RANGED FROM
1 - 4 DAYS), THE NEUTRON FLUX DISTRIBUTION IN THE EX-
TENDED TARGETS, THE EFFECTIVE NEUTRON TEMPERATURE, THE
NEUTRON CAPTURE CROSS SECTION OF THE TARGETS, THE
DECREASE OF THE NEUTRON FLUX IN THE TARGET, THE GAMMA
SELF-ABSORPTION IN THE TARGET AND THE ENERGY-, ANGLE-
AND DISTANCE-DEPENDENT EFFICIENCY OF THE DETECTOR.
TARGET AREA 4 X 16 CM-SQ, AT 15 DEG ANGLE TO BEAM AXIS
.GAMMA LINE ENERGY FOR THIS TARGET NOT MEASURED.
